metadata.name: Her Majesty - Queen Elizabeth II
metadata.description: The first stamp of Her Majesty's Joy.  The British Royal Family's postage stamp collection, or the Royal Philatelic Collection, is among the world's largest and most valuable in the world. The Queen took great pride in her collection, and this piece honors her remarkable life and her love for collecting small pieces of history.  The 1926 editions of this stamp honor the Queen's birth year.
